HEADWORD: Luteic
<hw>Lu*te"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>Pertaining to, or derived from, weld (<spn>Reseda
luteola</spn>).</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Pertaining to, or designating,
an acid resembling luteolin, but obtained from the flowers of
<spn>Euphorbia cyparissias</spn>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lutein</ent>⟦br⟧
